title: Coroner identifies woman found shot next to South area railroad tracks
text:
Coroner identifies woman found shot next to South area railroad tracks 
Residents reported hearing gunshots late Sunday evening 
Covering crime, police and courts in the Sacramento region 
By Bill Lindelof 
blindelof@sacbee.com 
The Sacramento County Coroner’s Office has released the name of a woman who was found dead with a gunshot wound on Monday near South area railroad tracks. 
She was identified as 54-year-old Anna Bernaix. A hometown was not listed on the coroner’s website for Bernaix. 
Sacramento County sheriff's detectives investigating the death of Bernaix said her body was discovered about 9 a.m. Monday near railroad tracks behind and just north of Gwinhurst Circle, which is near Calvine and Elk Grove Florin roads. 
Initially, the sheriff's department stated that Bernaix had head trauma and that further investigation was needed to discover how she died. Later in the week, detectives determined that she was the victim of homicide. 
During a canvass of the area, deputies talked to people who reported hearing gunshots late Sunday evening. 
No arrests have been made in the case.
